WEBVTT

00:01.353 --> 00:04.913
_

00:05.894 --> 00:07.762
[Speaks Hungarian]

00:07.764 --> 00:09.396
Scotch, neat.

00:09.398 --> 00:10.632
Make it a double.

00:17.873 --> 00:19.807
[English accent]
That good, eh?

00:21.143 --> 00:24.411
Let's see.
I lost my job today.

00:24.413 --> 00:27.047
Top it all off,
they canceled my flight.

00:27.049 --> 00:28.915
Ouch.

00:28.917 --> 00:30.751
Sorry.

00:30.753 --> 00:33.454
I'm a journalist.
That comes with the territory.

00:35.089 --> 00:36.723
You religious?

00:36.725 --> 00:38.592
Seriously?

00:38.594 --> 00:40.427
That's the line
you're going with?

00:40.429 --> 00:46.432
No, I'm just curious if
you believe in a higher power.

00:48.569 --> 00:53.774
Imagine if the world
had utterly changed,

00:53.776 --> 00:55.608
and no one had noticed a thing.

00:55.610 --> 00:58.178
I'm talking about

00:58.180 --> 01:00.513
an international
stealth operation

01:00.515 --> 01:04.016
to acquire and shutter
every company

01:04.018 --> 01:06.118
researching
artificial intelligence.

01:06.120 --> 01:07.353
Artificial intelligence?

01:07.355 --> 01:08.688
That's a real thing?

01:08.690 --> 01:10.756
Oh, it's here.

01:10.758 --> 01:14.526
I think an AI slipped
into the world unannounced,

01:14.528 --> 01:18.497
then set out to strangle
its rivals in the crib.

01:18.499 --> 01:19.999
And I know I'm on to something,

01:20.001 --> 01:23.135
because my sources keep
disappearing.

01:23.137 --> 01:24.937
My editor got reassigned.

01:24.939 --> 01:26.706
And now my job's gone.

01:26.708 --> 01:28.507
More and more,
it just feels like

01:28.509 --> 01:30.975
I was the only one
investigating the story.

01:32.512 --> 01:34.279
[Chuckling]
I'm sorry.

01:34.281 --> 01:37.683
I'm sure I sound like
a real conspiracy nut.

01:39.051 --> 01:40.686
<i>(Woman)</i>
<i>No, I understand.</i>

01:40.688 --> 01:42.387
You're saying
an artificial intelligence

01:42.389 --> 01:45.691
bought your paper
so you'd lose your job

01:45.693 --> 01:47.792
and your flight would
be canceled.

01:47.794 --> 01:52.797
And you'd end up
back at this bar...

01:52.799 --> 01:55.200
[Dramatic music]

01:55.202 --> 01:57.802
...where the only security camera
would go out.

01:59.671 --> 02:01.840
<i>And the bartender would</i>
<i>have to leave suddenly</i>

02:01.842 --> 02:04.975
<i>after getting</i>
<i>an emergency text.</i>

02:04.977 --> 02:07.911
The world has changed.

02:07.913 --> 02:10.247
You should know you're not the
only one who figured it out.

02:10.250 --> 02:12.182
You're one of three.

02:12.184 --> 02:14.518
The other two will die
in a traffic accident

02:14.520 --> 02:17.087
in Seattle in 14 minutes.

02:17.089 --> 02:18.356
[Gunshot]

02:18.358 --> 02:21.358
[Tense music]

02:21.360 --> 02:22.365
♪

02:22.366 --> 02:24.442
_

02:24.443 --> 02:26.905
_

02:34.005 --> 02:37.006
(Garrison) I have to say, the
early results are impressive.

02:37.008 --> 02:39.709
Samaritan has preempted
multiple threats

02:39.711 --> 02:41.077
to National Security.

02:41.079 --> 02:43.179
You're welcome, Senator.

02:43.181 --> 02:44.581
Your machine seems to be

02:44.583 --> 02:47.729
even more aggressive
than Northern Lights.

02:47.764 --> 02:48.618
[Cell phone vibrates]

02:48.619 --> 02:50.280
_

02:50.288 --> 02:53.756
Samaritan is designed
to be proactive.

02:53.758 --> 02:57.459
We can't afford to miss
even one terrorist now, can we?

02:57.461 --> 03:00.263
All assurances aside,

03:00.265 --> 03:03.032
what really concerns me
is accountability.

03:04.868 --> 03:06.936
Accountability?

03:06.938 --> 03:09.605
It appears Decima Technology
has been dismantled

03:09.607 --> 03:13.208
as a viable business entity,
which makes me wonder,

03:13.210 --> 03:15.577
who exactly is getting
the NSA feeds?

03:15.579 --> 03:17.212
We had a deal, Senator.

03:17.214 --> 03:18.914
We get the feeds.

03:18.916 --> 03:20.749
You get the relevant numbers.

03:20.751 --> 03:24.753
What we do with that information
is entirely up to us.

03:24.755 --> 03:27.923
That deal offered us
plausible deniability.

03:27.925 --> 03:30.391
If the public ever gets
wind of Samaritan,

03:30.393 --> 03:32.760
I just hope you're somewhere
to be found.

03:35.998 --> 03:39.734
I wonder if our...
fine Senator

03:39.736 --> 03:43.604
has become more of a problem
than asset.

03:43.606 --> 03:46.407
One that needs
to be eliminated.

03:47.209 --> 03:49.000
_

03:49.010 --> 03:53.147
And what about Harold Finch
and his associates?

03:53.668 --> 03:56.310
_

03:56.318 --> 03:58.252
Oh, that's unlike you.

03:58.254 --> 04:02.489
Still, I'm sure whatever rock
they decide to hide under,

04:02.491 --> 04:06.160
we'll find them as soon
as they emerge.

04:07.919 --> 04:10.408
_

04:10.409 --> 04:13.268
_

04:13.269 --> 04:16.603
_

04:17.438 --> 04:20.106
[Muzak playing]

04:20.108 --> 04:22.108
[Coughing]

04:22.110 --> 04:23.610
You must be allergic.

04:23.612 --> 04:25.545
- Oh!
- Whoops.

04:25.547 --> 04:27.947
Certainly looking
fierce today, sweetheart.

04:27.949 --> 04:30.984
Unfortunately, we hired you
to sell this stuff,

04:30.986 --> 04:32.718
not scare off the customers.

04:32.720 --> 04:33.987
Lady over there's been waiting

04:33.989 --> 04:35.488
15 minutes for a makeover.

04:35.490 --> 04:38.657
Now put on a smile
and snap to it, will you?

04:38.659 --> 04:41.660
[Dramatic music]

04:41.662 --> 04:50.302
♪

04:50.304 --> 04:54.172
Okay, this day job thing,
not really working out.

04:54.174 --> 04:55.841
Sorry, Sam.

04:55.843 --> 04:57.576
You need an identity.

04:57.578 --> 05:00.178
And you need to
trust the machine.

05:00.180 --> 05:02.080
Wait, the machine put me
in this silly-ass job?

05:02.082 --> 05:03.883
It's the only way to
keep you alive

05:03.885 --> 05:05.650
and off Samaritan's radar.

05:05.652 --> 05:09.754
For what it's worth,
I really like the new look.

05:09.756 --> 05:12.857
You're definitely an Autumn.

05:12.859 --> 05:14.192
I could stab you
with my stiletto.

05:14.194 --> 05:16.094
Enough already.

05:16.096 --> 05:18.196
Now when are we
getting new numbers?

05:18.198 --> 05:19.998
Keep it down.

05:20.000 --> 05:21.866
The machine has its reasons.

05:21.868 --> 05:23.401
Stay in character.

05:23.403 --> 05:26.237
Follow the calendar
on the phone I gave you.

05:26.239 --> 05:28.072
Check Angler.

05:28.074 --> 05:29.340
Maybe find a match.

05:29.342 --> 05:30.341
A match?

05:30.343 --> 05:31.876
As in a date?

05:31.878 --> 05:33.912
Make it look good.

05:33.914 --> 05:38.782
But for now, I need you
to make <i>me</i> look good.

05:39.784 --> 05:44.388
New job interview.

05:44.390 --> 05:48.292
Just promise me
John's a barista.

05:48.294 --> 05:51.295
[Suspenseful music]

05:51.297 --> 05:59.302
♪

06:00.772 --> 06:02.072
Why down here, yo?

06:02.074 --> 06:04.708
NYPD's got cams
all over the city.

06:04.710 --> 06:06.309
You can't be too careful.

06:06.311 --> 06:07.578
Where's the product?

06:07.580 --> 06:11.747
♪

06:11.749 --> 06:13.583
<i>(Man)</i>
<i>Uncut Afghan snow.</i>

06:13.585 --> 06:16.086
It stamped?

06:16.088 --> 06:17.087
Where'd you get it from?

06:17.089 --> 06:18.221
Enough talk.

06:18.223 --> 06:19.456
Show us the damn money.

06:19.458 --> 06:21.491
It's in the trunk.

06:21.493 --> 06:29.298
♪

06:29.300 --> 06:30.566
(Man)
It's all here.

06:32.235 --> 06:33.469
We'll take that.

06:33.471 --> 06:35.972
Matter of fact,
we'll take it all.

06:35.974 --> 06:37.840
This is where you get off.

06:37.842 --> 06:39.108
You don't want to do that.

06:39.110 --> 06:40.309
Oh, no?

06:40.311 --> 06:41.477
Waste this bitch.

06:41.479 --> 06:42.478
[Gun cocks]

06:42.480 --> 06:44.279
[Grunts]

06:44.281 --> 06:45.514
[Gunshots]

06:45.516 --> 06:48.517
[Sirens wailing]

06:52.688 --> 06:53.955
Down on the ground.

06:53.957 --> 06:56.325
Hands behind your head.

06:56.327 --> 06:59.328
[Dramatic music]

06:59.330 --> 07:00.662
♪

07:00.664 --> 07:02.196
Detective?

07:02.198 --> 07:03.532
You okay?

07:03.534 --> 07:05.433
Escort these clowns to the ER.

07:05.435 --> 07:07.201
Get the drugs and money
to evidence.

07:07.203 --> 07:09.170
Gotta go.

07:09.172 --> 07:11.506
Sir, don't you need
to file a report,

07:11.508 --> 07:13.274
firing your service weapon?

07:13.276 --> 07:15.043
It wasn't my weapon.

07:17.612 --> 07:20.614
[Quirky music]

07:20.616 --> 07:23.484
♪

07:23.486 --> 07:24.718
Hello.

07:24.720 --> 07:26.454
My name is Professor Whistler,

07:26.456 --> 07:28.722
and I'll be teaching
this semester's course

07:28.724 --> 07:29.990
on the ethics of...

07:29.992 --> 07:32.626
high-frequency
decision making.

07:32.628 --> 07:34.061
<i>[Student yawns]</i>

07:34.063 --> 07:35.996
Which I will endeavor
to make more interesting

07:35.998 --> 07:36.997
than that sounds.

07:36.999 --> 07:39.399
[Laughs]

07:39.401 --> 07:41.468
You all should've receive
a copy of the syllabus

07:41.470 --> 07:45.338
along with a list of
general guidelines

07:45.340 --> 07:48.909
and appropriate expectations.

07:48.911 --> 07:50.177
As a visiting associate,

07:50.179 --> 07:52.245
my office hours will be limited.

07:52.247 --> 07:53.480
All grades are final,

07:53.482 --> 07:55.182
so please, don't come to see me

07:55.184 --> 07:58.585
expecting to negotiate
a higher grade.

08:01.422 --> 08:02.822
Later.

08:06.660 --> 08:07.894
All right then.

08:07.896 --> 08:09.762
That concludes today's lecture.

08:09.764 --> 08:11.530
Your reading assignments
will be posted

08:11.532 --> 08:13.099
on the department website.

08:13.101 --> 08:14.500
Thank you.

08:16.937 --> 08:18.437
Come on, Bear.

08:18.439 --> 08:21.741
Professor, given
the modest number of students

08:21.743 --> 08:23.675
who have signed up
to take your course,

08:23.677 --> 08:25.578
the department may be
relocating you

08:25.580 --> 08:27.012
to a smaller venue.

08:27.014 --> 08:28.347
I see.

08:28.349 --> 08:30.782
Oh, and I managed
to make it through

08:30.784 --> 08:32.183
your dissertation.

08:32.186 --> 08:34.620
I found it a very...

08:34.621 --> 08:36.422
interesting read.

08:37.957 --> 08:40.692
Not quite certain how
you were able to obtain

08:40.693 --> 08:43.461
a $9 million grant
for such an obscure field.

08:43.462 --> 08:46.364
Took the liberty of
flagging a few typos.

08:46.366 --> 08:48.767
Certainly.
Thank you.

08:48.769 --> 08:51.202
Oh, one more thing.

08:51.204 --> 08:54.572
We do have a no dogs
on campus rule.

08:54.574 --> 08:56.941
Precedent.
You understand.

08:58.977 --> 09:02.113
- [Bear whines]
- [Cell phone beeps]

09:02.961 --> 09:05.020
_

09:06.718 --> 09:08.786
Not the first corner boy
to catch a bullet

09:08.788 --> 09:10.788
on these rooftops.

09:10.790 --> 09:11.889
This place is like

09:11.891 --> 09:13.824
a shooting range
for gangbangers.

09:13.826 --> 09:17.662
(Reese) What brings you up
to The Bronx, Detective?

09:17.664 --> 09:19.730
<i>(Fusco) Last I checked,
I was in Homicide.</i>

09:19.732 --> 09:21.331
This here looks like a body.

09:21.333 --> 09:24.501
What's Narcotics
doing here, <i>Detective?</i>

09:24.503 --> 09:26.637
Felix here was an affiliate
of a street gang

09:26.639 --> 09:28.238
taking over the heroin trade.

09:28.240 --> 09:30.607
Yeah, well,
now he's unaffiliated.

09:30.609 --> 09:32.842
If he was dealing, we didn't
find no junk on him.

09:32.844 --> 09:34.110
No bank neither.

09:34.112 --> 09:37.247
Wire strippers.

09:37.249 --> 09:40.450
What's this kid doing up here
with a pair of crimpers?

09:40.452 --> 09:42.152
Maybe he was jacking cable,

09:42.154 --> 09:44.154
another favorite pastime
in this hood.

09:44.156 --> 09:46.156
He didn't even live
in the building, Fusco.

09:46.158 --> 09:47.590
Why don't you let
the task force

09:47.592 --> 09:49.358
conduct the investigation,
huh, Crockett?

09:49.360 --> 09:51.928
It's just a shame
I got here too late.

09:53.864 --> 09:55.598
You and your old pals
used to be pretty good

09:55.600 --> 09:57.333
at getting out in front
of this type of stuff.

09:57.335 --> 09:59.535
What are you doing
fooling around in Narcotics?

09:59.537 --> 10:01.537
You gonna tell me
what's going on?

10:01.539 --> 10:03.038
[Cell phone beeps]

10:03.040 --> 10:04.973
- When I figure it out, Lionel...
- _

10:04.975 --> 10:06.875
...you'll be the first to know.

10:09.713 --> 10:11.647
[Cell phone beeps]

10:11.649 --> 10:12.981
<i>(Man) We all want to
push the negativity...</i>

10:12.983 --> 10:14.383
All right, already.
I'm here.

10:14.385 --> 10:16.652
<i>And open ourselves up</i>
<i>to positivity.</i>

10:16.654 --> 10:18.153
Why?

10:18.155 --> 10:21.623
Because positive people
are happier people.

10:21.625 --> 10:25.227
So I'm gonna share with you
the secret

10:25.229 --> 10:28.197
of how to become more positive
in three simple steps.

10:28.199 --> 10:30.232
Oh, boy.

10:30.234 --> 10:32.334
- [Cell phone vibrates]
<i>(Man) - Number one.</i>

10:32.336 --> 10:34.336
- Make happiness a choice.
- _

10:34.338 --> 10:35.803
Romeo?

10:35.805 --> 10:36.904
I don't think so.

10:36.906 --> 10:39.040
<i>(Man)</i>
<i>Number two.</i>

10:39.042 --> 10:40.875
Decide to rid your life
of negativity.

10:40.877 --> 10:43.411
Be free from self-doubt.

10:43.413 --> 10:45.380
Be free from the doubters
<i>around you.</i>

10:45.382 --> 10:48.250
Is that your perfume?

10:48.252 --> 10:50.385
I could smell you
down the hall.

10:50.387 --> 10:52.519
<i>(Man) - I know you're gonna do it.</i>
<i>- [Groans]</i>

10:52.521 --> 10:55.489
Stupid day job.

10:55.491 --> 10:58.392
Name tag's a nice touch.

10:58.394 --> 11:00.261
<i>(Man) Happy people,
positive people...</i>

11:00.263 --> 11:01.929
What the hell
are you doing here?

11:01.931 --> 11:03.931
Calendar alert.

11:03.933 --> 11:05.499
Me too.

11:05.501 --> 11:07.068
Why are we both here?

11:07.070 --> 11:10.003
Because we're all here
for a reason, right?

11:12.874 --> 11:17.544
Number three,
look for the positive in life.

11:17.546 --> 11:19.280
- This sucks.
- [Groans]

11:19.282 --> 11:21.114
Excuse me.

11:21.116 --> 11:22.383
Excuse us.

11:25.286 --> 11:26.686
<i>(Man) Now, that wasn't
very positive...</i>

11:26.688 --> 11:27.854
(Shaw)
You're a cop?

11:29.290 --> 11:31.124
Hey, at least you get to
crack a few skulls,

11:31.126 --> 11:32.425
carry a gun.

11:32.427 --> 11:34.394
New job's got me
chasing junkies

11:34.396 --> 11:36.296
and bagging bodies
after the fact.

11:36.298 --> 11:37.730
Stupid cover jobs.

11:37.732 --> 11:39.065
What are we doing?

11:39.067 --> 11:41.367
'Cause if our <i>friend</i>
<i>has a plan,</i>

11:41.369 --> 11:42.602
I am not seeing it.

11:42.604 --> 11:45.805
[Phone ringing]

11:53.113 --> 11:55.648
[Electronic voices
speaking indistinctly]

12:03.790 --> 12:06.258
Looks like
we're back in business.

12:07.625 --> 12:10.382
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

12:12.000 --> 12:18.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

12:19.679 --> 12:20.710
_

12:20.714 --> 12:22.764
[Tense music]

12:23.718 --> 12:26.637
_

12:32.627 --> 12:35.227
How goes the day job,
Detective Riley?

12:35.229 --> 12:38.397
Personally, I prefer
my real job, Finch.

12:38.399 --> 12:40.232
Professor Whistler, please.

12:40.234 --> 12:42.201
We're getting
numbers again, Harold.

12:43.704 --> 12:46.739
We need to get back to work.

12:46.741 --> 12:49.274
I'm no longer
your coworker, Detective.

12:49.276 --> 12:51.276
I'm done taking orders
from a computer.

12:51.278 --> 12:53.545
I thought I made that clear
after it instructed us

12:53.547 --> 12:54.913
to kill a Congressman.

12:54.915 --> 12:57.916
It also helped us
to save Grace.

12:57.918 --> 12:59.951
And now more lives need saving.

12:59.953 --> 13:01.920
I'm not sure that's
what we were really doing.

13:01.922 --> 13:03.322
I've totaled the lives we saved

13:03.324 --> 13:05.257
against the deaths
that we've caused,

13:05.259 --> 13:07.658
and I'm afraid we've been
operating at a bit of a loss.

13:07.660 --> 13:08.960
People who would still be alive

13:08.962 --> 13:10.394
if we hadn't interfered.

13:10.396 --> 13:12.330
You don't know that.

13:12.332 --> 13:14.833
What would've happened
if we hadn't intervened?

13:14.835 --> 13:17.635
There is a larger power
in play now,

13:17.637 --> 13:20.805
one that we are presently
ill-equipped to face.

13:20.807 --> 13:22.941
- Samaritan.
- Please be quiet.

13:22.943 --> 13:25.075
Here...

13:25.077 --> 13:28.412
I could really use
your input on this one.

13:31.983 --> 13:33.951
Ali Hasan.

13:33.953 --> 13:36.086
Runs an electronics shop
in The Bronx.

13:36.088 --> 13:38.088
He's good with computers.

13:38.090 --> 13:39.823
Kind of like you, Harold.

13:39.825 --> 13:43.660
If you or Sameen or anyone else
attempt to intervene

13:43.662 --> 13:47.164
with these numbers, you will
surely find yourselves dead.

13:47.166 --> 13:48.598
We have to do something.

13:48.600 --> 13:49.933
We have no resources, John.

13:49.935 --> 13:51.101
The library's gone.

13:51.103 --> 13:53.003
So we'll get another place.

13:53.005 --> 13:54.972
Don't you understand?
They're always watching.

13:54.974 --> 13:56.473
We can't even talk
on the telephone.

13:56.475 --> 13:58.841
There is no sanctuary.

13:58.843 --> 14:00.510
You can't just be
the man in the suit.

14:00.512 --> 14:01.878
You're a cop now.
I'm a professor.

14:01.880 --> 14:02.879
That's just the way it is.

14:02.881 --> 14:06.616
We don't need jobs, Harold.

14:06.618 --> 14:08.385
We need a purpose.

14:08.387 --> 14:11.288
The world has changed, John.

14:11.290 --> 14:12.522
I'm sorry.

14:14.491 --> 14:17.860
Bear, <i>blijven.</i>

14:17.862 --> 14:19.561
For the time being, I think
he'll be happier with you.

14:19.563 --> 14:23.299
Well, if it's not about
helping the numbers anymore,

14:23.301 --> 14:24.533
then what?

14:27.805 --> 14:30.005
It's about survival, John.

14:32.491 --> 14:35.627
_

14:39.215 --> 14:42.217
[Tense music] _

14:42.219 --> 14:44.420
♪

14:44.422 --> 14:47.588
(Hasan) Ben, I'm
back from lunch.

14:47.590 --> 14:53.661
♪

14:53.663 --> 14:55.263
[Door beeps]

14:57.733 --> 14:59.434
We got a problem, yo.

15:00.569 --> 15:02.070
How can I help?

15:02.072 --> 15:03.504
<i>(Man)</i>
<i>Don't play, old man.</i>

15:03.506 --> 15:05.506
We got a communications
breakdown.

15:05.508 --> 15:07.942
First you rat our burners out
to NYPD,

15:07.944 --> 15:09.944
the ones you sold us.

15:09.946 --> 15:11.779
Now your new phones
ain't working right.

15:11.781 --> 15:14.615
Way I see it,
you owe us a whole new system.

15:14.617 --> 15:16.016
<i>(Ben) Everything all right, dad?</i>

15:17.586 --> 15:19.887
Not if you don't get
those web orders boxed

15:19.889 --> 15:21.421
for FedEx by 3:00 PM.

15:21.423 --> 15:24.558
<i>Go.</i>

15:24.560 --> 15:26.961
I held up my end.

15:26.963 --> 15:28.795
I gave your men
all the equipment.

15:28.797 --> 15:30.297
I even told them
how to set it up.

15:30.299 --> 15:32.366
Yeah, the problem is,
our boy Felix caught

15:32.368 --> 15:34.634
a bullet on the rooftops.

15:34.636 --> 15:36.302
So now you're gonna
finish the job.

15:37.638 --> 15:38.638
_

15:38.639 --> 15:41.475
Dominic wants the new network up
and running in the next 48.

15:41.477 --> 15:43.142
I cannot be involved in this.

15:43.144 --> 15:45.211
It's a little late
for that, isn't it?

15:45.213 --> 15:46.980
Get your boy to help you out.

15:46.982 --> 15:48.415
You leave him out of this.

15:48.417 --> 15:49.949
I'm just saying,
you got a lot of people

15:49.951 --> 15:51.785
counting on you now, don't you?

15:51.787 --> 15:53.452
Clock is ticking.

15:53.454 --> 15:55.922
<i>(Ben) These are
ready to go, pop.</i>

15:55.924 --> 15:58.624
Anything else?

16:00.794 --> 16:04.063
48 hours, old man.

16:04.065 --> 16:06.599
[Door beeps]

16:06.601 --> 16:10.603
Let's go.

16:10.605 --> 16:12.137
[Door beeps]

16:12.139 --> 16:18.477
♪

16:18.479 --> 16:20.312
Can I help you find something?

16:20.314 --> 16:21.847
Wire crimpers.

16:21.849 --> 16:22.981
Ben.

16:22.983 --> 16:30.789
♪

16:30.791 --> 16:32.190
(Reese) Perfect match,
don't you think?

16:32.192 --> 16:34.426
This kid ever been
in your store before?

16:34.428 --> 16:38.196
Found him on a rooftop
a couple blocks from here

16:38.198 --> 16:40.966
with a pair of wire crimpers
just like these.

16:40.968 --> 16:43.668
Lots of places sell them.

16:43.670 --> 16:46.003
I wish I could help you more.

16:46.005 --> 16:50.642
You're a smart guy,
good with computers.

16:50.644 --> 16:52.444
You're a very private person,
aren't you, Ali?

16:56.482 --> 16:57.882
I think you're in trouble.

16:57.884 --> 17:01.185
I think I can help you.

17:01.187 --> 17:03.821
Going gets tough, call me.

17:05.958 --> 17:07.223
[Door beeps]

17:07.226 --> 17:09.359
Why didn't you just tell him?

17:09.362 --> 17:10.361
<i>These are bad guys.</i>

17:10.363 --> 17:11.362
We're in over our heads.

17:11.364 --> 17:12.964
Let me handle this, Ben.

17:12.965 --> 17:15.231
I built this store.
I won't be bullied.

17:15.233 --> 17:17.067
This is not
the old country, dad.

17:17.069 --> 17:18.868
You can talk to the police.

17:18.871 --> 17:21.304
<i>Talking to the police is</i>
<i>what got us in this mess.</i>

17:21.306 --> 17:23.406
I will mind my business.

17:23.407 --> 17:25.742
You will mind yours.

17:28.145 --> 17:30.246
[Phone rings] _

17:30.248 --> 17:31.814
This is Link.
Leave a message.

17:31.816 --> 17:33.216
- [Phone beeps]
(Hasan) - I fixed it.

17:33.218 --> 17:34.584
Meet me in Times Square.

17:34.586 --> 17:36.086
I'll give you
a phone that works.

17:38.389 --> 17:41.191
So what's this Egyptian guy
have to do with my DOA?

17:41.193 --> 17:44.227
Felix was in a gang
called The Brotherhood.

17:44.229 --> 17:46.596
Near as I can tell,
they're forcing Ali to build

17:46.598 --> 17:48.564
some kind of
private phone network

17:48.566 --> 17:50.165
the cops can't tap.

17:50.167 --> 17:52.234
So they're meeting in
Times Square for more privacy?

17:52.236 --> 17:53.402
For the people.

17:53.404 --> 17:54.937
<i>There's too many signals.</i>

17:54.939 --> 17:58.007
NYPD can't pinpoint
who's calling who.

17:58.009 --> 18:00.576
Ali's smart.
These guys are too.

18:00.578 --> 18:03.513
(Link)
Old man.

18:03.515 --> 18:05.780
The network should
be up and running.

18:05.782 --> 18:09.584
Because of the tall buildings,
the battery drains quickly.

18:09.586 --> 18:12.021
You need an extra battery pack.

18:12.023 --> 18:13.222
Dominic wants signal

18:13.224 --> 18:14.923
from the East River
to the Hudson.

18:14.925 --> 18:16.892
That will take
a little bit more time.

18:16.894 --> 18:21.062
But you can check the signal
up to five blocks east.

18:21.064 --> 18:24.032
Stay here.
I'm gonna call you in five.

18:24.034 --> 18:26.367
This better work.

18:26.369 --> 18:29.370
[Tense music]

18:29.372 --> 18:32.607
♪

18:32.609 --> 18:34.876
Ali's tracking Link's phone.

18:34.878 --> 18:35.877
[Car door clicks]

18:35.879 --> 18:38.546
Keep an eye on him.

18:38.548 --> 18:45.953
♪

18:45.955 --> 18:48.289
It looks like your guy's
sending a text.

18:50.992 --> 18:52.060
That's not a text.

18:52.062 --> 18:53.827
That's a detonation code.

18:53.829 --> 18:54.962
<i>The battery's a bomb.</i>

18:54.964 --> 18:56.163
Ali's not the victim.

18:56.165 --> 18:57.164
He's the perpetrator.

18:57.166 --> 19:00.167
[Dramatic music]

19:00.169 --> 19:05.472
♪

19:05.474 --> 19:06.807
[Glass shatters]
- [Grunts]

19:06.809 --> 19:08.609
[Tires squealing]

19:10.478 --> 19:11.911
[Grunts]

19:11.913 --> 19:16.149
♪

19:16.151 --> 19:17.417
[Cell phone beeping]

19:21.789 --> 19:27.293
♪

19:37.949 --> 19:40.117
(Fusco) You're full of
surprises, Mr. Hasan.

19:40.119 --> 19:41.618
Turning your cell phone

19:41.620 --> 19:43.420
into a remotely-detonated
explosive device.

19:43.422 --> 19:44.587
Where'd you learn that?

19:44.589 --> 19:47.123
I'm guessing Egyptian military,

19:47.125 --> 19:50.927
unit 777.

19:54.298 --> 19:57.233
The Brotherhood
is threatening you.

19:57.235 --> 19:59.768
We can help you,
Mr. Hasan,

19:59.770 --> 20:01.737
but you have to talk to us.

20:04.507 --> 20:07.676
I came to the police once.

20:07.678 --> 20:09.078
Gave you the serial numbers

20:09.080 --> 20:11.613
of the phones they purchased
from my store.

20:11.615 --> 20:12.949
You did nothing.

20:12.951 --> 20:14.783
They know you are listening
to them.

20:14.785 --> 20:17.152
They know where
your cameras are.

20:17.154 --> 20:19.688
They are smarter than you.

20:19.690 --> 20:22.257
This Dominic, he wanted you
to build some kind of

20:22.259 --> 20:24.092
private phone network.

20:24.094 --> 20:27.028
It doesn't matter anymore.

20:27.030 --> 20:30.665
You couldn't protect me,
so I protected myself,

20:30.667 --> 20:33.101
my store,

20:33.103 --> 20:34.869
my family.

20:34.871 --> 20:38.039
That's why I had to act.

20:38.041 --> 20:39.540
They threatened my son.

20:39.542 --> 20:40.708
Where's your son right now?

20:40.710 --> 20:42.877
Why do you want to know?

20:42.879 --> 20:44.212
Link isn't dead.

20:44.214 --> 20:45.280
What?

20:45.282 --> 20:46.647
- He escaped.
- What?

20:46.649 --> 20:48.683
How?
Ben.

20:48.685 --> 20:50.785
We'll call your son on the way.

20:50.787 --> 20:52.520
Let's go.

20:52.522 --> 20:54.522
(Hasan)
Ben?

20:54.524 --> 20:56.123
Ben?

20:56.125 --> 20:57.658
<i>(Reese) Keep him
back there, Lionel.</i>

20:57.660 --> 20:59.193
- Ben?
- Hey.

20:59.195 --> 21:00.862
<i>Oh, no.</i>

21:00.864 --> 21:02.563
[Gun cocks]
It's all clear. He's not here.

21:02.565 --> 21:03.830
They took my son.

21:03.832 --> 21:07.801
[Cell phone ringing]

21:07.803 --> 21:10.804
[Dramatic music]

21:10.806 --> 21:15.242
♪

21:15.244 --> 21:16.243
[Cell phone beeps]

21:16.245 --> 21:18.045
Hello.

21:18.047 --> 21:19.746
<i>(Link) Hey, old man,
you know who this is?</i>

21:19.748 --> 21:21.314
Yes.

21:21.316 --> 21:22.916
Yeah, you took your shot,
<i>but you missed.</i>

21:22.918 --> 21:24.584
<i>Now I've got your boy.</i>

21:24.586 --> 21:26.586
And you got till midnight
<i>to get the network up,</i>

21:26.588 --> 21:28.421
or he won't be coming home.

21:28.423 --> 21:30.490
<i>Don't waste time</i>
<i>going to the cops.</i>

21:30.492 --> 21:31.725
<i>You know we see them coming.</i>

21:31.727 --> 21:33.660
[Line clicks, phone beeps]

21:33.662 --> 21:35.428
What have I done?

21:35.430 --> 21:37.030
We're gonna help you,
Mr. Hasan.

21:37.032 --> 21:38.264
How?

21:38.266 --> 21:40.033
By getting your son back.

21:40.035 --> 21:43.069
You?
Haven't you done enough?

21:43.071 --> 21:45.338
Not yet, I haven't.

21:45.340 --> 21:47.006
Keep an eye on him.

21:51.578 --> 21:54.580
[Cell phone rings]

21:56.016 --> 21:58.216
- Hello.
(Reese) - Hey, it's me.

21:58.218 --> 22:00.452
I need you to drop
the eyeliner, pick up a gun,

22:00.454 --> 22:02.788
and help me take down
a criminal street gang.

22:02.790 --> 22:05.357
I'd really like to,

22:05.359 --> 22:09.094
but that sounds
like a bad idea.

22:09.096 --> 22:10.795
That's what Fusco says.

22:10.797 --> 22:12.730
I guess I'm full of them today.

22:12.732 --> 22:15.467
(Shaw) You go off the
reservation, they'll find you.

22:15.469 --> 22:17.869
And if you go down,
we all go down.

22:17.871 --> 22:20.305
We have a chance to get out
ahead of this one.

22:20.307 --> 22:22.274
I'm going in
with or without you.

22:22.276 --> 22:23.542
[Line clicks, phone beeps]

22:23.544 --> 22:25.610
[Sighs]

22:25.612 --> 22:28.613
[Dramatic music]

22:28.615 --> 22:35.419
♪

22:35.421 --> 22:38.723
[Grenade launcher booms,
glass shatters]

22:38.725 --> 22:39.958
[Explosion booms]
[Yells]

22:39.960 --> 22:43.427
[High-pitched tone]

22:43.429 --> 22:46.430
[Dramatic music]

22:46.432 --> 22:52.002
♪

22:52.004 --> 22:53.637
Where's the kid?

22:53.639 --> 22:55.806
What kid, man?

22:55.808 --> 22:57.174
The one Link kidnapped.

22:57.176 --> 22:59.242
Your punk ass is crazy.

22:59.244 --> 23:02.613
- [Guns cock]
- Yeah?

23:02.615 --> 23:05.515
You know, you really shouldn't
hold those things sideways.

23:05.517 --> 23:07.084
You can't aim,
and they'll eject

23:07.086 --> 23:08.652
a shell casing into your--

23:08.654 --> 23:10.821
Ah, forget it.

23:10.823 --> 23:15.592
[Men grunting, glass shattering]

23:15.594 --> 23:17.760
[Grunts]

23:17.762 --> 23:19.529
Last chance.
Where's Link?

23:19.531 --> 23:21.498
Man, Link bringing
in The Whale.

23:21.500 --> 23:22.499
The Whale?

23:22.501 --> 23:23.766
[Dramatic musical flourish]

23:23.768 --> 23:25.001
[Thud]

23:28.372 --> 23:30.773
I told you it was a bad idea.

23:48.229 --> 23:49.830
In her defense,
she had to work quickly.

23:51.566 --> 23:53.133
Professor.

23:55.870 --> 23:57.471
One moment, please.

23:59.006 --> 24:00.240
[Door clicks]

24:00.242 --> 24:03.310
What brings you here today,
Ms. Groves?

24:03.312 --> 24:07.080
Your former associates,
the mayhem twins.

24:07.082 --> 24:08.649
They're back to
trying to save people.

24:08.651 --> 24:10.249
I'm aware.

24:10.251 --> 24:11.918
Then you're also aware
that they're gonna

24:11.920 --> 24:15.155
get themselves caught
or killed without your help.

24:15.157 --> 24:18.224
I explained as much to John,
though I'm not sure

24:18.226 --> 24:20.994
how long they'd survive
even with my assistance.

24:20.996 --> 24:22.762
I assure you, the outcome
will be determined

24:22.764 --> 24:24.497
if you don't get involved.

24:24.499 --> 24:26.499
And this advice
is coming from you,

24:26.501 --> 24:28.401
Ms. Groves,
or from the machine?

24:28.403 --> 24:31.504
Now's not the time
to be precious, Harold.

24:31.506 --> 24:33.739
You don't get to
sit this one out.

24:33.741 --> 24:35.941
The world can't afford
to indulge your indecision.

24:35.943 --> 24:38.010
Oh, I think I made
my decision quite clear.

24:38.012 --> 24:39.345
Sorry.

24:39.347 --> 24:42.447
You have to pick a side,
because this is war.

24:42.449 --> 24:44.049
And the thing we're up against,

24:44.051 --> 24:47.019
it has virtually
unlimited resources,

24:47.021 --> 24:49.221
governments working unwittingly
at its behest,

24:49.223 --> 24:51.890
operatives around the globe
protecting it.

24:51.892 --> 24:54.059
You know how many we have?

24:54.061 --> 24:56.095
Five.

24:56.097 --> 24:59.464
Six, if you count the dog.

24:59.466 --> 25:02.267
You have a god
in this fight, Harold,

25:02.269 --> 25:04.302
and she's fighting for her life.

25:04.304 --> 25:05.437
I wouldn't know.

25:05.439 --> 25:06.871
She only talks to you,
Ms. Groves.

25:06.873 --> 25:09.574
Just because you stopped
listening to her

25:09.576 --> 25:13.878
doesn't mean
she isn't looking out for you.

25:13.880 --> 25:19.117
This job, your identity,
is her keeping you alive.

25:19.119 --> 25:21.953
She has the plan, Harold,

25:21.955 --> 25:24.922
but she needs you to sit up
and pay attention.

25:24.924 --> 25:27.258
To what, the numbers?

25:27.260 --> 25:31.229
In the face of such a struggle,
saving one or two people,

25:31.231 --> 25:32.796
what difference
would that make?

25:32.798 --> 25:33.964
Every life matters.

25:33.966 --> 25:35.766
You taught me that.

25:35.768 --> 25:40.003
The numbers, our identities,
they all mean something.

25:40.005 --> 25:42.139
It all adds up to something.

25:42.141 --> 25:44.642
All of this matters.
We all matter.

25:49.613 --> 25:52.615
You got your friends
into this mess.

25:52.617 --> 25:55.152
Least you can do
is get them out of it.

25:56.788 --> 25:58.789
[Door slams]

25:58.791 --> 26:01.792
[Reese groaning]

26:06.530 --> 26:08.598
What happened?

26:08.600 --> 26:10.266
I saved your ass.

26:10.268 --> 26:11.267
That's what happened.

26:11.269 --> 26:13.770
I had things in hand, Shaw.

26:13.772 --> 26:16.272
Yeah, things like
a grenade launcher.

26:16.274 --> 26:19.008
You can't do that
anymore, Reese.

26:19.010 --> 26:20.209
Neither of us can.

26:20.211 --> 26:23.212
We get caught, we get exposed,

26:23.214 --> 26:24.213
and then it's lights out.

26:24.215 --> 26:26.548
[Cell phone vibrates] _

26:27.851 --> 26:30.953
Ugh.
No means no, asshat.

26:30.955 --> 26:32.888
I need to get back to work.

26:32.890 --> 26:35.024
I might still need
your help, Shaw.

26:35.026 --> 26:36.491
Did you not hear
anything I just said?

26:36.493 --> 26:37.959
Yeah, I did.

26:37.961 --> 26:40.228
But I'm also trying
to save a kid.

26:42.565 --> 26:43.965
You had to put it that way.

26:43.967 --> 26:45.701
[Sighs]

26:47.203 --> 26:49.003
(Hasan) You said you
would get my son back.

26:49.005 --> 26:50.238
And I will.

26:52.342 --> 26:55.310
If you can't find Ben,
I must have this network up

26:55.312 --> 26:56.577
before midnight.

26:56.579 --> 26:59.080
I have gone over
everything I can think of,

26:59.082 --> 27:01.415
but it still won't connect.

27:01.417 --> 27:03.718
(Finch) Perhaps I can
be of some assistance.

27:03.720 --> 27:07.088
[Tense music]

27:07.090 --> 27:10.391
Detective Fusco said
I might find you here.

27:10.393 --> 27:11.659
Who are you?

27:11.661 --> 27:13.060
He's a friend.

27:14.830 --> 27:17.197
Do you know anything about
wireless network architecture?

27:17.199 --> 27:18.733
A bit.

27:18.735 --> 27:20.267
I think you'll find
I'm a quick study.

27:20.269 --> 27:21.435
I'll leave you to it.

27:21.437 --> 27:22.703
I'm gonna track down Link.

27:22.705 --> 27:24.872
Detective, whatever your plans,

27:24.874 --> 27:26.407
I urge you to be discreet.

27:26.409 --> 27:28.108
Our current circumstances
require

27:28.110 --> 27:29.676
that we play by the rules.

27:29.678 --> 27:32.346
So then I'll find
someone who doesn't.

27:41.289 --> 27:42.555
Phone.

27:42.557 --> 27:44.257
[Phone thuds]

27:44.259 --> 27:46.225
[Door slams]

27:46.227 --> 27:49.228
[Tense music]

27:49.230 --> 27:54.868
♪

27:54.870 --> 27:57.136
Hello, John.

27:57.138 --> 28:01.107
♪

28:01.109 --> 28:03.609
How many nodes
are in the network?

28:03.611 --> 28:05.978
Honestly, I don't even know.

28:05.980 --> 28:08.047
I should've never agreed
to build this thing

28:08.049 --> 28:10.549
in the first place.

28:10.551 --> 28:12.151
Look, why don't we start over?

28:12.153 --> 28:14.420
Tell me how you constructed
the network.

28:14.422 --> 28:18.156
Maybe it's better
if I just showed you.

28:19.325 --> 28:21.293
This is it.

28:21.295 --> 28:23.328
This is one of my routers.

28:25.899 --> 28:27.733
How large is
your coverage area?

28:27.735 --> 28:29.401
- All five boroughs.
- All five?

28:29.403 --> 28:30.436
Yes.

28:30.438 --> 28:31.737
Installing that many antennas

28:31.739 --> 28:33.271
would surely raise
some suspicion.

28:33.273 --> 28:34.439
That's just it.

28:34.441 --> 28:35.840
They didn't have
to install them.

28:35.842 --> 28:38.009
The antennas were
already there.

28:40.947 --> 28:43.514
VHF television antennas.

28:43.516 --> 28:47.185
You can still find them
on most rooftops in the city.

28:49.355 --> 28:51.589
Huh.

28:51.591 --> 28:53.324
It's been too long, John.

28:53.326 --> 28:55.626
What have you been up to?

28:55.628 --> 28:57.962
It's...

28:57.964 --> 28:59.330
complicated.

28:59.332 --> 29:03.434
Well, now that is
an unexpected development.

29:03.436 --> 29:05.770
What can I do for you,
Detective?

29:05.772 --> 29:07.104
I'm looking for information

29:07.106 --> 29:09.106
on a gang
called The Brotherhood.

29:09.108 --> 29:11.475
They kidnapped a kid,
and I want him back.

29:11.477 --> 29:14.278
Sorry to say I don't know much
about this Brotherhood.

29:14.280 --> 29:16.380
It's run by a guy
named Dominic.

29:16.382 --> 29:17.647
We haven't met yet.

29:17.649 --> 29:20.684
Do you know
why they took the kid?

29:20.686 --> 29:22.453
They're squeezing
his old man to build

29:22.455 --> 29:24.120
some kind of
communications network

29:24.122 --> 29:25.655
the cops can't tap.

29:25.657 --> 29:29.659
They gave him a deadline,
midnight,

29:29.661 --> 29:31.027
or they'll kill his son.

29:31.029 --> 29:32.896
Why midnight?

29:32.898 --> 29:35.799
Might have to do with someone
called The Whale.

29:35.801 --> 29:39.202
I heard they're bringing him
in for a meeting.

29:39.204 --> 29:41.304
The Whale isn't a person, John.

29:41.306 --> 29:43.139
It's a shipment of heroin.

29:43.141 --> 29:46.242
Four times a year,
a truck comes up from Mexico.

29:46.244 --> 29:48.844
It's driven to a location,
usually a house,

29:48.846 --> 29:52.715
and for one night, the most
protected house in the city.

29:52.717 --> 29:55.318
And there it's cut
and packaged for couriers

29:55.320 --> 29:59.221
waiting to deliver it
all along the eastern seaboard.

29:59.223 --> 30:02.256
HR used to handle The Whale,

30:02.258 --> 30:05.092
but since their demise,
the cartel's struggled

30:05.094 --> 30:07.094
to find a reliable partner.

30:07.096 --> 30:10.398
It could be Dominic
creating his own opportunity.

30:10.400 --> 30:12.767
Ambitious and smart.

30:12.769 --> 30:15.236
Reminds me of me in my youth.

30:15.238 --> 30:16.838
A little advice, Detective,

30:16.840 --> 30:19.873
maybe steer clear
of this Dominic.

30:19.875 --> 30:21.742
I'm afraid I can't do that.

30:21.744 --> 30:25.746
Which brings me to
the other reason I'm here.

30:28.083 --> 30:30.117
I'd like to hire you.

30:35.423 --> 30:37.591
Well, I think I may have found
a way to fix your network.

30:37.593 --> 30:38.725
How?

30:38.727 --> 30:40.093
I've written a firmware patch

30:40.095 --> 30:42.462
that should allow the nodes
to handle

30:42.464 --> 30:44.197
an increased number
of connections.

30:44.199 --> 30:45.899
<i>I'm uploading it now.</i>

30:45.901 --> 30:48.068
It's working.

30:48.070 --> 30:50.136
<i>The network is up.</i>

30:50.138 --> 30:52.072
You did it.
[Laughs]

30:52.074 --> 30:54.907
No, you did,
Mr. Hasan.

30:54.909 --> 30:57.110
You took an obsolete
and forgotten technology

30:57.112 --> 31:00.613
and created a modern, invisible
communications network.

31:03.150 --> 31:05.651
I just did it to get Ben back.

31:05.653 --> 31:07.753
Then we have
little time to waste.

31:09.056 --> 31:12.124
[Cell phone rings]

31:12.126 --> 31:13.158
Yeah.

31:13.160 --> 31:14.493
It's Ali.

31:14.495 --> 31:16.328
The network is up.
You can use it.

31:16.330 --> 31:17.797
(Link)
That's good.

31:17.799 --> 31:20.066
Guess what you needed was
the right motivation, huh?

31:20.068 --> 31:21.601
(Hasan) I gave you
what you wanted.

31:21.603 --> 31:23.335
Now give me back my son.

31:23.337 --> 31:25.737
Relax, old man.
You're gonna get him.

31:25.739 --> 31:27.473
But right now I'm in
the middle of something.

31:27.475 --> 31:30.442
Sit tight.
I'll be in touch.

31:30.444 --> 31:31.943
What?

31:31.945 --> 31:35.314
Hello?

31:35.316 --> 31:36.915
Now what?

31:36.917 --> 31:39.951
Now we call John.

31:39.953 --> 31:42.487
You put a lot of trust
in your friend.

31:42.489 --> 31:45.123
I do.

31:45.125 --> 31:48.026
In all the time I've known him,
he's never let me down.

31:49.495 --> 31:51.663
[Cell phone beeps]

31:52.661 --> 31:54.204
_

31:59.971 --> 32:01.339
[Cell phone rings]

32:01.341 --> 32:02.340
Hello?

32:02.342 --> 32:03.841
It's me.

32:03.843 --> 32:05.476
I'm borrowing
the gang's mesh network.

32:05.478 --> 32:06.644
<i>I'm sending you</i>
<i>the location of the node</i>

32:06.646 --> 32:08.112
<i>they're connected to.</i>

32:08.114 --> 32:10.214
They should be within
a few hundred feet.

32:10.216 --> 32:13.217
I'm on my way.
I'll let Shaw know.

32:13.219 --> 32:14.952
John, remember to be careful.

32:14.954 --> 32:17.454
Just like old times,
huh, Finch?

32:17.456 --> 32:20.124
Hardly, Detective.

32:20.126 --> 32:23.193
[Tires squeal]

32:23.195 --> 32:24.394
[Cell phone beeps]

32:24.396 --> 32:26.163
Network's up.

32:26.165 --> 32:28.999
Dominic says he wants everyone
rolling out in 30 minutes.

32:29.001 --> 32:31.468
What about the kid?

32:31.470 --> 32:34.471
[Tense music]

32:34.473 --> 32:39.309
♪

32:39.311 --> 32:42.245
As soon as we're done here,
we'll take him back to his pops.

32:42.247 --> 32:43.913
♪

32:43.915 --> 32:46.349
Then we throw them
both in the river.

32:46.351 --> 32:50.086
♪

33:02.342 --> 33:04.543
(Reese)
Shaw, you in position?

33:04.545 --> 33:06.678
Yeah, at least until the owners
come home from dinner.

33:06.680 --> 33:08.414
[Gun clicks]

33:08.416 --> 33:11.017
All right, I got eyes on.

33:11.019 --> 33:12.385
(Reese)
Copy. Stand by.

33:12.387 --> 33:14.720
Now, just remember,
Reese, you're NYPD.

33:14.722 --> 33:16.088
You go all Rambo,

33:16.090 --> 33:17.823
I won't be there to bail
you out this time.

33:17.825 --> 33:19.758
(Reese)
I'm a reformed man, Shaw,

33:19.760 --> 33:22.227
following the rules
and keeping a low profile.

33:22.229 --> 33:25.230
[Suspenseful music]

33:25.232 --> 33:26.331
Let's go.

33:26.333 --> 33:28.099
We got a dozen cars moving out,

33:28.101 --> 33:30.201
every brick,
every borough tonight.

33:30.203 --> 33:32.905
♪

33:32.907 --> 33:35.273
<i>(Man)</i>
<i>Look out!</i>

33:35.275 --> 33:38.276
[Metal crashing,
glass shattering]

33:40.847 --> 33:44.882
♪

33:44.884 --> 33:46.217
[Sighs]

33:46.219 --> 33:47.585
That's your idea
of a low profile?

33:52.558 --> 33:54.124
What the hell?

33:54.126 --> 33:56.060
<i>What's going on?</i>

33:56.062 --> 33:57.795
Beats me.

33:57.797 --> 34:01.131
Appears to be some kind
of traffic accident.

34:04.436 --> 34:06.571
[Man gasping, coughing]

34:06.573 --> 34:08.272
Elias says hello.

34:17.815 --> 34:21.051
Looks like a gang dispute
over drugs.

34:21.053 --> 34:24.120
The SUV was coming from
that house, which gives me

34:24.121 --> 34:26.956
probable cause
to take a closer look.

34:26.958 --> 34:29.059
Got your back, Detective.

34:29.061 --> 34:30.827
Go check it out.

34:30.829 --> 34:32.629
Anybody comes near
this place, kill them.

34:35.065 --> 34:37.000
Bag it all up.

34:37.002 --> 34:38.835
We're moving out.

34:38.837 --> 34:41.337
Yo, if you see something,
shoot it.

34:41.339 --> 34:43.072
[Guns cock]

34:43.074 --> 34:44.440
- [Gunshots]
- [Grunts]

34:44.442 --> 34:45.674
[Grunts]

34:45.676 --> 34:46.742
[Gun clicks]

34:46.744 --> 34:49.011
[Gunshots]
- [Grunts]

34:49.013 --> 34:50.012
[Grunts]

34:51.681 --> 34:53.782
Took care of
your welcoming party.

34:53.784 --> 34:55.184
They didn't look too friendly.

34:55.186 --> 34:58.186
[Suspenseful music]

34:58.188 --> 35:02.424
♪

35:02.426 --> 35:03.659
[Grunts]

35:03.661 --> 35:06.261
[All yelling]

35:06.263 --> 35:07.262
[Gunshot]

35:07.264 --> 35:08.363
[Grunts]

35:08.365 --> 35:13.201
♪

35:13.203 --> 35:14.769
[Sirens wailing]

35:14.771 --> 35:17.705
Reese, your buddies in blue
are getting close.

35:17.707 --> 35:19.874
I have to find Ben.

35:19.876 --> 35:22.877
[Music intensifies]

35:22.879 --> 35:28.517
♪

35:28.519 --> 35:30.217
<i>He's gone.</i>

35:30.219 --> 35:32.153
So is Link.

35:32.155 --> 35:33.721
<i>(Shaw)</i>
<i>I got 'em.</i>

35:33.723 --> 35:35.023
They went out the back.

35:37.059 --> 35:38.693
I can't get a clear shot.

35:41.363 --> 35:44.032
[Keys jingle,
engine turns over]

35:44.034 --> 35:46.833
Hey again.

35:46.835 --> 35:48.335
[Grunting]

35:49.871 --> 35:52.072
Time's up.

35:52.074 --> 35:53.073
Good luck, Reese.

36:00.882 --> 36:01.915
Down on the ground!

36:01.917 --> 36:03.516
Finally.

36:03.518 --> 36:06.219
It's good to see you guys.

36:06.221 --> 36:08.689
Riley, Narcotics.

36:13.027 --> 36:15.696
[Cell phone vibrates]

36:15.698 --> 36:16.830
John?

36:16.832 --> 36:18.264
(Reese)
Put Ali on.

36:23.070 --> 36:25.037
- Hello?
(Ben) - Dad?

36:25.039 --> 36:27.406
Ben.

36:27.408 --> 36:28.874
Are you all right?

36:28.876 --> 36:30.009
Did they hurt you?

36:30.011 --> 36:31.243
I'm okay.

36:31.245 --> 36:33.278
They destroyed the store.

36:33.280 --> 36:35.514
It doesn't matter.

36:35.516 --> 36:36.515
You're all right.

36:36.517 --> 36:39.518
That's all that matters.

36:39.520 --> 36:41.553
It was never about the store.

36:41.555 --> 36:43.054
But they'll come back.

36:43.056 --> 36:46.325
So we will move.

36:46.327 --> 36:48.993
We are the store, Ben.

36:48.995 --> 36:51.330
You and me.

36:51.332 --> 36:54.499
Just come home.

36:59.071 --> 37:02.073
[Tense music] _

37:02.075 --> 37:04.075
♪

37:04.077 --> 37:05.710
Whoa, whoa.

37:05.712 --> 37:08.346
[American accent] Meg
Watkins, Homeland Security.

37:08.348 --> 37:09.580
What happened here?

37:09.582 --> 37:11.682
Gang war over drugs, ma'am.

37:11.684 --> 37:12.917
Gangs?

37:12.919 --> 37:18.188
♪

37:18.190 --> 37:19.690
I don't think so.

37:19.692 --> 37:21.459
Ma'am?

37:21.461 --> 37:29.467
♪

37:34.877 --> 37:41.491
_

37:46.217 --> 37:51.888
I think I know why the machine
chose this time to resurface.

37:51.890 --> 37:53.290
It wanted you to help
the number,

37:53.292 --> 37:56.159
but it also wanted
a number to help you.

37:56.161 --> 37:57.160
[Zipper scratching]

38:01.799 --> 38:04.267
[Clears throat]

38:04.269 --> 38:06.836
(Reese)
It's Ali's mesh network.

38:06.838 --> 38:08.671
What about The Brotherhood?

38:08.673 --> 38:11.174
I expect they believe
the NYPD confiscated it.

38:11.176 --> 38:13.442
But just to be safe,
I've augmented these phones

38:13.444 --> 38:15.744
with a rolling
encryption algorithm.

38:15.746 --> 38:18.414
You and Sameen will
be able to communicate

38:18.416 --> 38:20.516
without fear of
anyone else listening,

38:20.518 --> 38:22.484
including Samaritan.

38:28.157 --> 38:32.328
It's not just about
the numbers, Harold.

38:32.330 --> 38:34.697
It's about survival.

38:43.005 --> 38:44.706
Be safe, John.

38:51.380 --> 38:52.680
Bear, <i>volg.</i>

39:03.392 --> 39:04.892
[Stapler clicks]

39:04.894 --> 39:08.062
Didn't teach you knots
in Girl Scouts?

39:09.798 --> 39:11.398
Are you checking up on me?

39:11.400 --> 39:13.901
I worry about you, Sameen.

39:13.903 --> 39:16.536
I also have a black-tie
dinner tonight,

39:16.538 --> 39:19.907
and I need a new polish,
something bold.

39:19.909 --> 39:23.744
Oh, and you should
check your calendar.

39:23.746 --> 39:25.812
I think you have a coffee date.

39:25.814 --> 39:28.181
[Sighs]
No way.

39:28.183 --> 39:29.983
The machine stuck me
in this retail hell.

39:29.985 --> 39:32.018
There's no way I'm letting it
near my love life.

39:32.020 --> 39:34.320
She has a reason
for everything,

39:34.322 --> 39:36.022
even if sometimes
it requires you to act

39:36.024 --> 39:38.592
like a well-adjusted
member of society.

39:38.594 --> 39:40.226
Trust her.

39:40.228 --> 39:42.362
[Nail polish bottles clicking]

39:42.364 --> 39:45.365
[Tense music]

39:45.367 --> 39:49.502
♪

39:49.504 --> 39:50.503
<i>(Fusco)</i>
<i>Hey.</i>

39:52.039 --> 39:54.440
- What are you doing?
- IT, dude.

39:54.442 --> 39:56.509
Just setting up
your partner's computer.

39:56.511 --> 39:58.278
Whoa, what do you mean?
What partner?

39:58.280 --> 40:00.379
Some hotshot,
just made a big bust,

40:00.381 --> 40:01.614
got promoted from Narcotics.

40:01.616 --> 40:03.215
[Door clicks]

40:03.217 --> 40:05.017
He can tell you all about it.

40:05.019 --> 40:07.052
Detective.

40:07.054 --> 40:08.521
You?

40:08.523 --> 40:09.789
You guys know each other?

40:09.791 --> 40:11.624
We've met.

40:11.626 --> 40:13.692
All set.

40:13.694 --> 40:15.127
Make yourself at home.

40:27.540 --> 40:29.374
Welcome to the Eighth.

40:29.376 --> 40:30.775
[Dark, brooding music]

40:30.777 --> 40:34.946
♪ everywhere is freaks
and hairies ♪

40:34.948 --> 40:37.782
♪ dykes and fairies ♪

40:37.784 --> 40:40.051
- ♪ tell me, where is sanity? ♪
- _

40:40.053 --> 40:47.792
♪

40:47.794 --> 40:50.061
♪ tax the rich ♪

40:50.063 --> 40:52.396
♪ feed the poor ♪

40:52.398 --> 40:56.267
♪ till there are no rich
no more ♪

40:56.269 --> 41:01.439
♪

41:01.441 --> 41:07.444
♪ I'd love to change
to the world ♪

41:07.446 --> 41:10.080
♪ but I don't know what to do ♪

41:10.082 --> 41:15.986
♪

41:15.988 --> 41:20.624
♪ so I'll leave it up to you ♪

41:20.626 --> 41:22.625
♪

41:22.627 --> 41:26.863
♪ population keeps on
breeding ♪

41:26.865 --> 41:30.600
♪ nation bleeding ♪

41:30.602 --> 41:33.870
♪ still more feeding economy ♪

41:33.872 --> 41:41.544
♪

41:41.546 --> 41:43.212
♪ life is funny ♪

41:43.214 --> 41:45.848
♪ skies are sunny ♪

41:45.850 --> 41:48.017
♪ bees make honey ♪

41:48.019 --> 41:49.652
♪ who needs money ♪

41:49.654 --> 41:54.156
♪

41:54.158 --> 41:57.626
Sameen?

41:57.628 --> 41:59.028
Romeo.

41:59.030 --> 42:00.529
I've been looking
for a good match.

42:00.531 --> 42:03.032
Thought you might
not be interested.

42:03.034 --> 42:05.734
- Just careful.
- Us too.

42:05.736 --> 42:07.736
I hear you're looking
for some real work.

42:10.540 --> 42:12.407
We need a good wheelman.

42:13.743 --> 42:15.209
Interested?

42:15.211 --> 42:17.913
Absolutely.

42:17.915 --> 42:25.654
♪

42:25.656 --> 42:29.690
♪ oh, oh ♪

42:29.692 --> 42:35.696
♪ but I don't know what to do ♪

42:35.698 --> 42:38.166
♪

42:38.168 --> 42:39.767
♪ but I don't know ♪

42:39.769 --> 42:43.771
♪ what to do ♪

42:43.773 --> 42:46.874
♪ oh, oh ♪

42:46.876 --> 42:52.512
♪ but I don't know what to do ♪

42:52.514 --> 42:55.515
♪ whoa, oh oh, oh, oh ♪

42:55.517 --> 43:00.353
♪ but I don't know what to do ♪

